snippet: The Federal Trade Commission concluded that the company had not harmed competition, but regulators must remain watchful.
abstract: Editorial contends Federal Trade Commission's conclusion that Google is not manipulating search results in way that harms consumers does not completely settle question of whether company has abused its dominance as search engine; calls on antitrust regulators to remain watchful.
lead_paragraph: The Federal Trade Commission concluded that the company had not harmed competition, but regulators must remain watchful.
